## Avoid Deep Nesting!

```python
if a:
    if b:
        if c:
            if d:
                # Too deep! Hard to read!
                do_something()
```

Deeply nested code is hard to read and maintain.

slides.codeSnippet:
# Instead of nested
age = 25
has_id = True
is_member = True

# Flat and clear
if age >= 18 and has_id and is_member:
    print("VIP access granted!")
elif age >= 18 and has_id:
    print("Regular access granted.")
elif age >= 18:
    print("Please show ID.")
else:
    print("Sorry, adults only.")

