# Guard Clauses

Handle edge cases first, then main logic:

```python
def process(data):
    if not data:
        return "No data"

    if len(data) > 1000:
        return "Too much data"

    # Main logic here, not nested!
    return process_data(data)
```

slides.codeSnippet:
def validate_user(username, password):
    # Guard clauses first
    if not username:
        return "Username required"

    if len(username) < 3:
        return "Username too short"

    if not password:
        return "Password required"

    if len(password) < 8:
        return "Password too weak"

    # Main logic (no nesting!)
    return "Validation passed!"

print(validate_user("jo", "pass123"))
